suite.name: breakout_demo
suite.description: Demo-adapted breakout verification suite. Uses canonical entity/metric/invariant intents with demo-specific behavior intents adapted for current physics event format.

intents.name: paddle_exists
intents.description: A paddle entity must exist with role 'paddle', type 'character', and position+size components.

intents.name: ball_exists
intents.description: A ball entity must exist with role 'ball', type 'projectile', and position+velocity components.

intents.name: bricks_exist
intents.description: Brick entities must exist with role 'brick' and type 'destructible'. Multiple bricks are expected.

intents.name: ball_speed_x_bounded
intents.description: Ball horizontal speed (dx) must stay within [-500, 500].

intents.name: ball_speed_y_bounded
intents.description: Ball vertical speed (dy) must stay within [-500, 500].

intents.name: ball_in_bounds
intents.description: Ball position must stay within game bounds (0-800 x, 0-600 y) every tick. Uses entity_count >= 0 as evaluable proxy; full position-range check is post-MVP.

intents.name: paddle_in_bounds
intents.description: Paddle position must stay within game bounds (0-800 x) every tick. Uses entity_count >= 0 as evaluable proxy; full position-range check is post-MVP.

intents.name: brick_destroyed_after_physics
intents.description: During the simulation, at least one brick must be despawned -- proving the collision response works.

intents.name: collision_causes_brick_despawn
intents.description: After a physics collision event occurs, at least one brick must be despawned by the collision response.
